results.name: Number T(n,k) of entries in the k-th last blocks of all set partitions of [n]; triangle T(n,k), n>=1, 1<=k<=n, read by rows.
link: Alois P. Heinz, Rows n = 1..141, flattened
example: T(3,2) = 6 because the number of entries in the second last blocks of all set partitions of [3] (123, 12|3, 13|2, 1|23, 1|2|3) is 0+2+2+1+1 = 6.
xref: Columns k=1-2 give: A038561 (for n>1), A286433.
Main diagonal and first lower diagonal give: A000012, A000217.
results.author: _Alois P. Heinz_, May 08 2017
